Singapore's gross domestic productwill grow six pct in the first quarter and five pct in thesecond quarter this year, with further growth expected in thesecond half, Trade and Industry Minister Lee Hsien Loong toldparliament.    The figures compared with 3.4 pct contraction and 1.2 pctgrowth respectively for the first and second quarters of 1986.    The estimates were based on a tentative leading indicatorincorporating new business orders, company inventories andshare prices used by his ministry, Lee said, without givingfurther details of the new indicator.    Singapore's economy grew 1.9 pct last year, after shrinking1.8 pct in 1985. The government has forecast growth rate ofthree to four pct for 1987. REUTER&#3;